      },
      "date": "2018-03-29 08:50:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nIf I understand correctly by reading LU-10707, the purpose of this patch is to fix an issue found with broken TCP routed LNet traffic in Lustre 2.10. I am able to reproduce this issue on my test system. However, when I apply this patch on top of Lustre 2.10.3, the issue is not fixed.\nI also tested on master branch, but the TCP routed LNet traffic is not broken even without this patch.\nSo I put -1 here, although the patch in itself looks ok to me, until the situation is clarified.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
